<item>
            <title>[LU-8403] OBD_NOTIFY_* flags cleanup</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8403</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Half of the &lt;tt&gt;OBD_NOTIFY_*&lt;/tt&gt; flags are essentially useless but we still have code that used them. The useless ones are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;OBD_NOTIFY_CREATE
OBD_NOTIFY_CONNECT
OBD_NOTIFY_SYNC_NONBLOCK
OBD_NOTIFY_SYNC
OBD_NOTIFY_CONFIG
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Server side OBDs do not implement &lt;tt&gt;o_notify&lt;/tt&gt; and so the &lt;tt&gt;OBD_NOTIFY_CONFIG&lt;/tt&gt; notification in &lt;tt&gt;server_start_targets()&lt;/tt&gt; is useless and can be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;data&lt;/tt&gt; parameter of &lt;tt&gt;obd_notify()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;obd_notify_observer()&lt;/tt&gt; may be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lov_notify()&lt;/tt&gt; may be simplified by assuming that &lt;tt&gt;watched&lt;/tt&gt; is not NULL.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;OBD_NOTIFY_CONNECT&lt;/tt&gt; notification in &lt;tt&gt;lov_connect()&lt;/tt&gt; is useless and can be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;OBD_NOTIFY_ACTIVE&lt;/tt&gt; notification in &lt;tt&gt;lmv_connect_mdc()&lt;/tt&gt; is useless and can be rremoved.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lco_flags&lt;/tt&gt; is never checked in llite and can be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;enum config_flags&lt;/tt&gt; can be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
